  <part id="P1">
    <!--
      A delayed turn over a moving left-hand accompaniment, mirroring the gruppetti
      in Beethoven's Pathétique 2nd movement. The principal sounds on the beat and is
      held; the turn proper (D5, C5, B4, C5) is squeezed into the final sixteenth of
      the quarter note. The two inner left-hand sixteenths therefore fall BETWEEN the
      held principal and the turn, so they must be playable in between, not after the
      whole turn.

      Right hand (staff 1): C5 quarter with a delayed turn, then G5 quarter.
      Left hand  (staff 2): four C3 sixteenths, then a C3 quarter.

      In C major the turn on C5 expands to D5, C5, B4, C5. With the delay, the
      expected order is:
        beat 1 sixteenth 1: C5  + C3   (principal struck on the beat)
        beat 1 sixteenth 2:       C3   (held principal, left hand alone)
        beat 1 sixteenth 3:       C3   (held principal, left hand alone)
        beat 1 sixteenth 4: D5  + C3   (turn begins, with the 4th left-hand note)
                            C5, B4, C5  (rest of the turn)
        beat 2:             G5  + C3
    -->
